msgstr "2. The training rule on physical contact"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.199"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-ss.2.1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.2.1.1"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa993"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anātha­piṇḍi­"
"kassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā udāyī araññe viharati."
msgstr "At that time Venerable Udāyī was staying in the wilderness."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.1.3"
msgid ""
"Tassāyasmato vihāro abhirūpo hoti dassanīyo pāsādiko, majjhegabbho, "
"saman­tā­pariyā­gāro,"
msgstr ""
"He had a beautiful dwelling with a room in the middle and corridors on all "
"sides."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.1.4"
msgid "supaññattaṃ mañcapīṭhaṃ bhisi­bibbo­hanaṃ,"
msgstr "The bed and bench were nicely made up,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.1.5"
msgid "pānīyaṃ paribhojanīyaṃ sūpaṭṭhitaṃ,"
msgstr "and the water for drinking and that for washing had been well placed."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.1.6"
msgid "pariveṇaṃ susammaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr "The precincts were well swept."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.1.7"
msgid "Bahū manussā āyasmato udāyissa vihārapekkhakā āgacchanti."
msgstr "Many people came to see Udāyī’s dwelling."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa994"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.1.8"
msgid "Aññataropi brāhmaṇo sapajāpatiko yenāyasmā udāyī tenupasaṅkami;"
msgstr "Among them was a certain brahmin and his wife."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.1.9"
msgid "upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "They approached Udāyī and said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.1.10"
msgid "“icchāma mayaṃ bhoto udāyissa vihāraṃ pekkhitun”ti."
msgstr "“Venerable, we would like to have look at your dwelling.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.1.11"
msgid "“Tena hi, brāhmaṇa, pekkhassū”ti,"
msgstr "“Well then, brahmin, have a look.”"

#. </p><p>
#. VAR: avāpuraṇaṃ → apāpuraṇaṃ (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.1.12"
msgid "avāpuraṇaṃ ādāya ghaṭikaṃ ugghāṭetvā kavāṭaṃ paṇāmetvā vihāraṃ pāvisi."
msgstr ""
"Udāyī took the key, unlocked the bolt, opened the door, and entered the "
"dwelling."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.1.13"
msgid "Sopi kho brāhmaṇo āyasmato udāyissa piṭṭhito pāvisi."
msgstr "The brahmin entered after him"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.1.14"
msgid "Sāpi kho brāhmaṇī tassa brāhmaṇassa piṭṭhito pāvisi."
msgstr " and then the brahmin lady."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.1.15"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā udāyī ekacce vātapāne vivaranto ekacce vātapāne thakento "
"gabbhaṃ anuparigantvā piṭṭhito āgantvā tassā brāhmaṇiyā aṅgamaṅgāni parāmasi."
msgstr ""
"Opening some windows and closing others, Udāyī walked around the inner room "
"and came up from behind the brahmin lady, touching her here and there."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.200"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.1.16"
msgid "Atha kho so brāhmaṇo āyasmatā udāyinā saddhiṃ paṭisammoditvā agamāsi."
msgstr "Then the brahmin thanked Udāyī and departed."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.1.17"
msgid "Atha kho so brāhmaṇo attamano attamanavācaṃ nicchāresi—"
msgstr "The brahmin then expressed his delight,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.1.18"
msgid "“uḷārā ime samaṇā sakyaputtiyā ye ime evarūpe araññe viharanti."
msgstr "“These Sakyan ascetics who live in the wilderness are superb."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.1.19"
msgid "Bhavampi udāyī uḷāro yo evarūpe araññe viharatī”ti."
msgstr "Venerable Udāyī is superb!”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.120"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa995"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.1.20"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, sā brāhmaṇī taṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavoca—"
msgstr "But the brahmin lady said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.1.21"
msgid "“kuto tassa uḷārattatā."
msgstr "“What’s superb about him?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.1.22"
msgid ""
"Yatheva me tvaṃ aṅgamaṅgāni parāmasi evameva me samaṇo udāyī aṅgamaṅgāni "
"parāmasī”ti."
msgstr "Just as you touch me here and there, so did he.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.1.23"
msgid "Atha kho so brāhmaṇo ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—"
msgstr "The brahmin then complained and criticized him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.1.24"
msgid "“alajjino ime samaṇā sakyaputtiyā dussīlā musāvādino."
msgstr "“These Sakyan ascetics are shameless and immoral liars."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.1.25"
msgid ""
"Ime hi nāma dhammacārino samacārino brahmacārino saccavādino sīlavanto "
"kalyāṇadhammā paṭijānissanti."
msgstr ""
"They claim to live according to the Truth, to be celibate and of good "
"conduct, to be truthful, moral, and of good character."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.1.26"
msgid ""
"Natthi imesaṃ sāmaññaṃ natthi imesaṃ brahmaññaṃ, naṭṭhaṃ imesaṃ sāmaññaṃ "
"naṭṭhaṃ imesaṃ brahmaññaṃ,"
msgstr "But they don’t have the qualities of an ascetic or a brahmin."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.1.27"
msgid ""
"kuto imesaṃ sāmaññaṃ kuto imesaṃ brahmaññaṃ, apagatā ime sāmaññā apagatā ime "
"brahmaññā."
msgstr "They’ve lost the plot."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.1.28"
msgid "Kathañhi nāma samaṇo udāyī mama bhariyāya aṅgamaṅgāni parāmasissati."
msgstr "How can the ascetic Udāyī touch my wife with his genitals?"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.201"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.1.29"
msgid ""
"Na hi sakkā kulitthīhi kuladhītāhi kulakumārīhi kulasuṇhāhi kuladāsīhi "
"ārāmaṃ vā vihāraṃ vā gantuṃ."
msgstr ""
"It’s not possible to go to a monastery or a monk’s dwelling with wives of "
"respectable families, with daughters, girls, daughters-in-law, or female "
"slaves of respectable families."

#. VAR: Sace → sace hi (s1-3)
#. VAR: kuladhītaro → kuladhītayo (bj) | kuladhītāyo (si, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.1.30"
msgid ""
"Sace kulitthiyo kuladhītaro kulakumāriyo kulasuṇhāyo kuladāsiyo ārāmaṃ vā "
"vihāraṃ vā gaccheyyuṃ, tāpi samaṇā sakyaputtiyā dūseyyun”ti."
msgstr "If you do, the Sakyan ascetics might molest them.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.2.1.2"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa996"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.2.1"
msgid ""
"Assosuṃ kho bhikkhu tassa brāhmaṇassa ujjhāyantassa khiyyantassa "
"vipācentassa."
msgstr "The monks heard the criticism of that brahmin."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.2.2"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.2.3"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized Udāyī,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.2.4"
msgid ""
"“kathañhi nāma āyasmā udāyī mātugāmena saddhiṃ kāyasaṃsaggaṃ "
"samāpajjissatī”ti."
msgstr "“How can Venerable Udāyī make physical contact with a woman?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa997"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.2.5"
msgid ""
"Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ aneka­pariyā­yena vigarahitvā "
"bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "They then told the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.2.6"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṃghaṃ "
"sannipātāpetvā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ paṭipucchi—"
msgstr "The Master had the Order of monks assembled and questioned Udāyī,"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.2.7"
msgid ""
"“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, udāyi, mātugāmena saddhiṃ kāyasaṃsaggaṃ samāpajjasī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, Udāyī, that you made physical contact with a woman?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.2.8"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.2.9"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā—"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.2.10"
msgid ""
"“ananucchavikaṃ, moghapurisa, ananulomikaṃ appatirūpaṃ assāmaṇakaṃ akappiyaṃ "
"akaraṇīyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“Foolish man, it’s not suitable, it’s not proper, it’s not worthy of a "
"recluse, it’s not allowable, it’s not to be done."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.2.11"
msgid ""
"Kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, mātugāmena saddhiṃ kāyasaṃsaggaṃ "
"samāpajjissasi."
msgstr "How can you make physical contact with a woman?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.2.12"
msgid ""
"Nanu mayā, moghapurisa, aneka­pariyā­yena virāgāya dhammo desito no sarāgāya "
"… pe …"
msgstr ""
"Haven’t I given many teachings for the sake of dispassion, not for the sake "
"of passion …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.2.13"
msgid "kāma­pari­ḷāhā­naṃ vūpasamo akkhāto."
msgstr "for the stilling of the fever for sense pleasures?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.2.14"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.2.15"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.2.15a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa998"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.202"></a>
#. <span class="rule"> 
#. VAR: veṇiggāhaṃ → veṇigāhaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
#. VAR: hatthaggāhaṃ → hatthagāhaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.2.16"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu otiṇṇo vipariṇatena cittena mātugāmena saddhiṃ "
"kāyasaṃsaggaṃ samāpajjeyya hatthaggāhaṃ vā veṇiggāhaṃ vā aññatarassa vā "
"aññatarassa vā aṅgassa parāmasanaṃ,"
msgstr ""
"‘If a lustful monk makes physical contact with a woman—holding her hand or "
"hair, or touching any part of her body—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.2.17"
msgid "saṃghādiseso”ti."
msgstr "he commits an offense entailing suspension.’”"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs1.2.18"
msgid "(<em>2</em>:<strong>6</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-ss.2.2"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-ss.2.2.1"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa999"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs2.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs2.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs2.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs2.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr ""
"… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order "
"through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs2.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli3.121"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1000"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs2.1.6"
msgid "Otiṇṇo nāma"
msgstr "Lustful:"

#. </span>
#. I have rendered <i lang="pli">otiṇṇo vipariṇatena cittena</i> with the single word “lustful.” This means that the definition for <i lang="pli">vipariṇataṃ</i> is missing from my translation. Here is the Pali, followed by a translation: <i lang="pli">Vipariṇatanti rattampi cittaṃ vipariṇataṃ. Duṭṭhampi cittaṃ vipariṇataṃ. Mūḷhampi cittaṃ vipariṇataṃ. Api ca rattaṃ cittaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetaṃ vipariṇatanti</i>; “distorted: a mind with desire is distorted, a mind with anger is distorted, a confused mind is distorted. But in this case ‘distorted’ refers to a mind with desire.”
#. <span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs2.1.7"
msgid "sāratto apekkhavā paṭi­baddha­citto."
msgstr "having lust, longing for, in love with."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1001"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs2.1.8"
msgid "Vipariṇatanti"
msgstr ""

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs2.1.9"
msgid "rattampi cittaṃ vipariṇataṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs2.1.10"
msgid "Duṭṭhampi cittaṃ vipariṇataṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs2.1.11"
msgid "Mūḷhampi cittaṃ vipariṇataṃ."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs2.1.12"
msgid "Api ca rattaṃ cittaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetaṃ vipariṇatanti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1002"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs2.1.13"
msgid "Mātugāmo nāma"
msgstr "A woman:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs2.1.14"
msgid "manussitthī, na yakkhī na petī, na tiracchānagatā."
msgstr ""
"a human female, not a female spirit, not a female ghost, not a female animal;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs2.1.15"
msgid "Antamaso tadahujātāpi dārikā, pageva mahattarī."
msgstr "even a girl born on that very day, all the more an older one."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1003"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs2.1.16"
msgid "Saddhinti"
msgstr "With:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs2.1.17"
msgid "ekato."
msgstr "together."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1004"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs2.1.18"
msgid "Kāyasaṃsaggaṃ samāpajjeyyāti"
msgstr "Makes physical contact:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs2.1.19"
msgid "ajjhācāro vuccati."
msgstr "misconduct is what is meant."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.1.203"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1005"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs2.1.20"
msgid "Hattho nāma"
msgstr "Hand:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs2.1.21"
msgid "kapparaṃ upādāya yāva agganakhā."
msgstr "from the elbow to the tip of the nails."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1006"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs2.1.22"
msgid "Veṇī nāma"
msgstr "Hair:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs2.1.23"
msgid ""
"suddhakesā vā, suttamissā vā, mālāmissā vā, hiraññamissā vā, suvaṇṇamissā "
"vā, muttāmissā vā, maṇimissā vā."
msgstr ""
"just the hair; or hair with strings in it, with a garland, with gold, with "
"pearls, or with gems."

#. </span>
#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="ms-pa" id="ms-pa1007"></a>
#. <span class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs2.1.24"
msgid "Aṅgaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Any part of her body:"

#. </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-ss2:pts-cs2.1.25"
